---
import ReportLayout from '@/components/ReportLayout.astro';
---

<ReportLayout title="Connecting Tokens Studio">

  <section class="guide-intro">
    <p class="guide-eyebrow">For the Myprotein design team</p>
    <h1 class="guide-h1">Connecting Tokens Studio</h1>
    <p class="guide-lead">
      Tokens Studio is the plugin that links Figma to the design system's token values —
      colour, spacing, border radius — which live in a GitHub repository. It's the bridge
      between "a value changed in the repo" and "that change shows up in your Figma library".
    </p>
    <p class="guide-lead">
      Most designers will never need to run a sync. This page is here for when you do, or
      when you just want to understand what's happening behind the scenes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 1 ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Installing the plugin</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Tokens Studio for Figma is a community plugin. In Figma, open the
      <strong>Plugins</strong> menu, search for <strong>"Tokens Studio for Figma"</strong>,
      and install it. It only needs to be installed once per machine — it's then available
      from the plugins menu in any file.
    </p>
    <div class="takeaway">
      <p class="takeaway-label">What to do instead</p>
      <p>
        Install it on the design system file specifically — that's the only file where syncing
        should happen. You shouldn't need it open in your own working files.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 2 ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Connecting to the repo</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Inside the plugin, go to <strong>Settings → Sync</strong> and add a GitHub provider
      pointing at <code>THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds/ux-prototyping</code> — the same repo this site
      lives in — on the <code>main</code> branch. This also needs a personal access token with
      access to the repo.
    </p>
    <div class="takeaway">
      <p class="takeaway-label">What to do instead</p>
      <p>
        If you don't have a token for this, ask the team before setting this up — don't
        generate one against a different repo or account. Getting this wrong can connect the
        library to the wrong source of truth.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 3 ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Pulling updates</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Once connected, the plugin shows a <strong>Pull</strong> option whenever the repo has
      changes that haven't been brought into Figma yet. Pulling updates the token values
      inside the plugin — colours, spacing, radius — to match what's in the repo.
    </p>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Pulling on its own doesn't update anyone's files. It just brings the latest values into
      this Figma file, ready to be applied.
    </p>
    <div class="takeaway">
      <p class="takeaway-label">What to do instead</p>
      <p>
        After pulling, quickly check what changed before moving on — the plugin shows a diff
        of old vs new values. If something looks unexpected, flag it before going further.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 4 ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Publishing the library</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Pulled values need to be applied to Figma's variables and then published as a library
      update — that's what makes the change visible to every connected working file. Once
      published, anyone with the library switched on will see the new values flow into their
      files automatically.
    </p>
    <div class="takeaway">
      <p class="takeaway-label">What to do instead</p>
      <p>
        If you're the one publishing, post in the team channel afterwards. A library update
        can shift things across multiple files at once — people should know it happened, even
        if nothing looks different to them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Closing ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-closing">
    <p>
      If you hit a permissions error, an unfamiliar repo, or a sync that looks like it's
      pulling the wrong values — stop and ask, rather than reconfiguring it yourself. This
      connection is shared infrastructure: a wrong setting here doesn't just affect your file,
      it affects everyone's.
    </p>
  </section>

</ReportLayout>

<style>
  .guide-intro { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .guide-eyebrow {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .guide-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 40px);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .guide-lead {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .guide-lead:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .guide-section {
    margin-bottom: 44px;
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .section-heading {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .guide-body {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .guide-body:last-of-type { margin-bottom: 16px; }

  .takeaway {
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-mint);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    padding: 14px 18px;
  }
  .takeaway-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 800;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.55;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .takeaway p:not(.takeaway-label) {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .takeaway code {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
  }

  .guide-closing {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-top: 56px;
    padding-top: 28px;
    border-top: 2px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .guide-closing p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .guide-h1 { font-size: 28px; }
    .section-heading { font-size: 18px; }
  }
</style>
